    {
        "content": "<p>uweigand created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12707#discussion_r2995933417\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This should be an <code>SImm20</code> to cover the full range of supported displacements.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 581976464,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1774540589
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>uweigand created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12707#discussion_r2995968983\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I think we need to ensure the inner <code>iadd</code> uses the proper type (I32) - otherwise we might incorrectly catch extends from I16 or I8.</p>\n<p>Also, I think we can support a non-zero offset32 field - this can just be passed to the <code>memarg_reg_plus_off</code> like usual (will be used as additional displacement in the actual memory access).</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 581976465,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1774540589
    },
